  "asset": "EURUSD",
  "timeframe": "1H",
  "market_context": "EUR/USD is in a daily downtrend with the daily range high taken out and price consolidating above the daily range low near equal lows. Expansion has occurred lower and the analyst is anticipating continuation lower toward the previous day's low and daily targets.",
  "key_observation": "The analyst tracks the trend lower by anticipating protected swing highs to form on the hourly: each time price sweeps a high and closes through the series of up-close candles, a new protected high is confirmed and continuation lower is anticipated.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Frame the daily context — range high taken out, equal lows below, expansion already lower, and consolidation, so a run of a high and protected swing formation is expected for continuation lower.",
    "Step 2: Anticipate the protected swing high on the daily and drop to the hourly chart to look for lower time frame setups and confirmations.",
    "Step 3: Identify the first sweep of a high with closure through the series of up-close candles, confirming a protected high and expectation of continuation lower.",
    "Step 4: Note the next reach into a fair value gap fails to deliver a protected swing — only a lethargic move back into range, so that high is not confirmed as protected.",
    "Step 5: Wait for the next sweep of a high and require a closure through the up-close candles; once closed through, treat the wick high as the new protected high.",
    "Step 6: Let price continue lower, taking out the previous day's low and approaching the range low.",
    "Step 7: On the next continuation leg, identify another sweep into a fair value gap; mark the level (C2) and wait for closure through the up-close candles to define a new protected high (C4 continuation).",
    "Step 8: Repeat the protected-swing tracking process to ride the continuation lower toward the daily target."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "Distinguish anticipating a protected swing from a confirmed one — only when price closes through the series of opposing candles after a sweep is the high protected. Lethargic returns into the range do not confirm a protected swing and should be skipped.",
